rump%20is%20threatening%20the%20very%20thing%20that%20gives%20NATO%20the%20strength%20to%20stand%20up%20to%20Russia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20pauses%20as%20he%20addresses%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20the%20second%20day%20of%20the%20North%20Atlantic%20Treaty%20Organization%20(NATO)%20summit%20in%20Brussels%20on%20July%2012%2C%202018.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ca83606e2e190e71a3ad78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20pauses%20as%20he%20addresses%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20the%20second%20day%20of%20the%20North%20Atlantic%20Treaty%20Organization%20(NATO)%20summit%20in%20Brussels%20on%20July%2012%2C%202018.%3Cp%3EBRENDAN%20SMIALOWSKI%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETrump%20said%20he'd%20encourage%20Russia%20to%20do%C2%A0%26quot%3Bwhatever%20the%20hell%20they%20want%26quot%3B%20to%20NATO%20members%20who%20aren't%20meeting%20spending%20expectations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETrump%20has%20long%20expressed%20criticisms%20of%20the%20alliance%2C%20spurring%20anxiety%20among%20European%20partners.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20newest%20remarks%20suggest%20he%20could%20degrade%20the%20foundational%20trust%20between%20NATO%20nations%2C%20threatening%20the%20alliance's%20strength.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20was%20out%20on%20the%20campaign%20trail%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20former%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20told%20supporters%20he'd%20encourage%20Russia%20to%20do%20%26quot%3Bwhatever%20the%20hell%20they%20want%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20NATO%20members%20who%20aren't%20paying%20their%20fair%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20sentiment%20isn't%20exactly%20new%20territory%20for%20Trump%2C%20who%20has%20long%20expressed%20a%20negative%2C%20distrustful%20view%20of%20NATO%2C%20but%20it%20is%20shockingly%20inflammatory%2C%20an%20open%20threat%20that%20the%20US%20won't%20hold%20up%20its%20end%20of%20the%20bargain%20and%20come%20to%20the%20aid%20of%20its%20allies%20should%20they%20be%20attacked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20specifically%2C%20it's%20a%20threat%20to%20Article%205%2C%20the%20thing%20that%20gives%20the%20NATO%20alliance%20the%20strength%20to%20stand%20up%20to%20challenges%20like%20Russian%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20resulting%20backlash%2C%20his%20allies%20dismissed%20the%20remark%20as%20just%20Trump%20being%20Trump%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F02%2F12%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-nato-republicans.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeven%20praised%20its%20frank%20honesty%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20few%2C%20if%20any%2C%20acknowledged%20what%20it%20shows%3A%20Trump%2C%20if%20reelected%2C%20doesn't%20need%20to%20remove%20the%20US%20from%20NATO%20to%20erode%20the%20binding%20trust%20that%20its%20members%20would%20defend%20one%20another%20should%20Russia%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Saturday%20at%20a%20rally%20in%20South%20Carolina%2C%20Trump%20said%20he%20once%20threatened%20a%20fellow%20%26quot%3Blarge%26quot%3B%20NATO%20country%20who%2C%20he%20said%2C%20had%20declined%20to%20spend%20the%202%25%20recommended%20equivalent%20of%20their%20GDP%20on%20NATO's%20collective%20defense%20but%20still%20wanted%20assurance%20that%20the%20US%20would%20help%20defend%20them%20should%20Russia%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20said%3A%20'You%20didn't%20pay%3F%20You're%20delinquent%3F'%20He%20said%3A%20'Yes%2C%20let's%20say%20that%20happened.'%20No%2C%20I%20would%20not%20protect%20you.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20would%20encourage%20them%20to%20do%20whatever%20the%20hell%20they%20want.%20You%20gotta%20pay%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20letting%20Russia%20do%20what%20it%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20move%20would%20be%20an%20outright%20dismissal%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nato.int%2Fcps%2Fen%2Fnatohq%2Ftopics_110496.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArticle%205%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20major%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20alliance%20that%20guarantees%20that%20if%20any%20NATO%20ally%20were%20a%20victim%20of%20an%20attack%2C%20every%20other%20member%20would%20join%20together%20in%20their%20defense.%20This%20offers%20collective%20defense%20and%20collective%20deterrence%20against%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArticle%205%20responses%20are%20not%20automatic%20and%20rely%20in%20part%20on%20political%20will%20and%20unwavering%20commitments%20from%20member%20nations%20to%20generate%20the%20desired%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22NATO%20navies%20Baltic%20Operations%20exercise%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656771d1fd6200867dd09f02%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221124%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShips%20from%20NATO%20navies%20sail%20in%20formation%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%20during%20the%20exercise%20Baltic%20Operations%202023%20on%20June%204%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%2FStaff%20Sgt.%20Shawn%20Coover%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20when%2C%20where%2C%20or%20even%20if%20this%20conversation%20Trump%20described%20took%20place.%20And%20like%20most%20of%20Trump's%20provocative%20and%20loud%20remarks%2C%20particularly%20on%20foreign%20policy%2C%20one%20questions%20whether%20they'll%20be%20reflected%20by%20his%20actual%20policy%20%E2%80%94%20or%20should%20even%20really%20be%20considered%20with%20any%20weight%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20his%20comments%20indicate%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2024%2F02%2F12%2Fdishonest-spending-rhetoric-that-masks-trumps-russia-sympathies%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efundamental%20misunderstanding%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20how%20NATO%20works%20and%20how%20the%20US%20benefits%20from%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20not%20any%20dues%20in%20the%20alliance%20but%20rather%20expectations%20that%20members%20of%20the%20largest%20military%20bloc%20in%20history%20will%20continue%20to%20invest%20in%20its%20success%20to%20deter%20an%20aggressive%20Russia%20and%20empower%20it%20to%20respond%20to%20other%20threats%20and%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20the%20US%20may%20be%20the%20largest%20funder%2C%20it%20reaps%20many%20of%20the%20benefits.%20With%20NATO%2C%20the%20US%20is%20surrounded%20by%20a%20dozens%20of%20partners%2C%20defended%20by%20guaranteed%20allies%20should%20it%20go%20to%20war%2C%20and%20supported%20economically%20and%20geopolitically%20amid%20rising%20tensions%20with%20potential%20adversaries.%20America's%20unipolar%20moment%20has%20passed%2C%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20having%20friends%20can't%20be%20overstated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20concept%20that%20Trump's%20former%20defense%20secretary%2C%20Jim%20Mattis%2C%20emphasized%20repeatedly%2C%20at%20one%20point%20telling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2019%2F09%2F02%2F756681750%2Fjim-mattis-nations-with-allies-thrive-nations-without-allies-wither%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENPR%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bthroughout%20history%2C%20we%20see%20nations%20with%20allies%20thrive%2C%20and%20nations%20without%20allies%20wither.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArticle%205%20has%20only%20been%20invoked%20once%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20alliance%2C%20and%20that%20was%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%209%2F11%20terror%20attacks%20on%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20latest%20remarks%20on%20NATO%20sparked%20anxieties%20in%20Europe%20and%20received%20significant%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20suggestion%20that%20allies%20will%20not%20defend%20each%20other%20undermines%20all%20of%20our%20security%2C%20including%20that%20of%20the%20US%2C%20and%20puts%20American%20and%20European%20soldiers%20at%20increased%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20NATO%20Secretary%20General%20Jens%20Stoltenberg%20said%20Sunday%2C%20highlighting%20the%20good%20faith%20needed%20between%20NATO%20allies%20to%20uphold%20Article%205%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20easily%20politics%20can%20poison%20critical%20trust.%20Trump%20stirred%20up%20feelings%20of%20uncertainty%20just%20with%20the%20mere%20suggestion%20the%20US%20wouldn't%20come%20to%20the%20aid%20of%20its%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20one-term%20presidency%2C%20Trump%20regularly%20criticized%20the%20alliance%2C%20calling%20out%20fellow%20NATO%20members'%20spending%20on%20the%20defense%20budget%20and%20suggesting%20it%20wasn't%20a%20fair%20deal%20for%20the%20US.%20He%20even%20privately%20discussed%20pulling%20out%20of%20NATO%20several%20times%2C%20administration%20officials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F01%2F14%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fnato-president-trump.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleaked%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReactions%20were%20volatile.%20Critics%20said%20the%20move%20would%20not%20only%20have%20destroyed%20over%2070%20years'%20worth%20of%20work%20and%20commitment%20from%20countless%20US%20policymakers%20and%20politicians%20but%20would%20have%20also%20given%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20the%20ultimate%20gift%20of%20a%20severely%20weakened%20NATO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20hurtles%20put%20in%20place%20to%20stop%20presidents%20from%20pulling%20out%20of%20NATO%2C%20but%20there%20are%20other%20ways%20to%20harm%20the%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nato%20military%20exercise%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5630db2ebd86eff45b8ba341%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Italian%20soldier%20is%20silhouetted%20during%20a%20NATO%20military%20exercise%20at%20the%20Birgi%20NATO%20Airbase%20in%20Trapani%2C%20Italy%20October%2019%2C%202015.%20NATO%20and%20its%20allies%20opened%20their%20largest%20military%20exercise%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20on%20Monday%2C%20choosing%20the%20central%20Mediterranean%20to%20showcase%20strengths%20that%20face%20threats%20from%20Russia's%20growing%20military%20presence%20from%20the%20Baltics%20to%20Syria.%3Cp%3ETony%20Gentile%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Trump%20very%20likely%20to%20be%20the%20Republican%20Party's%20nominee%20for%20the%20presidential%20election%20this%20year%2C%20questions%20remain%20over%20whether%20he'll%20try%20to%20pick%20up%20where%20he%20left%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20comments%20on%20Sunday%2C%20Stoltenberg%20said%20he%20expected%20%26quot%3Bthat%20regardless%20of%20who%20wins%20the%20presidential%20election%20the%20US%20will%20remain%20a%20strong%20and%20committed%20NATO%20ally%26quot%3B%20before%20further%20stressing%20that%20any%20attack%20on%20a%20NATO%20member%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bmet%20with%20a%20united%20and%20forceful%20response.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20discussion%20comes%20at%20a%20critical%20time%20for%20the%20alliance.%20NATO%20is%20facing%20a%20rather%20telling%20inflection%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20its%20members%20continue%20to%20increase%20their%20defense%20spending%20and%20heavily%20invest%20in%20military%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20against%20Russia.%20For%20the%20most%20part%2C%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20in%202022%20prompted%20the%20alliance%20to%20grow%20stronger%20and%20closer%2C%20much%20to%20Putin's%20dismay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20just%20last%20April%2C%20it%20gained%20a%20new%20member%2C%20Finland%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-member-finland-closing-border-says-russia-causing-migrant-situation-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efurther%20strengthening%20it%20against%20Russia%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sweden's%20ascension%20may%20be%20close.%20And%20Ukraine%20has%20expressed%20keen%20interest%20in%20joining%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20although%20that%20process%20will%20likely%20have%20to%20wait%20until%20the%20end