0question.%20The%20demolition%20of%20the%20mosque%20had%20a%20profound%20impact%20on%20their%20social%2C%20political%20and%20cultural%20outlook.%20I%20inherited%20that%20anxiety%20as%20I%20grew%20up%20mostly%20surrounded%20by%20my%20Muslim%20family.%20The%20accounts%20and%20narratives%20of%20my%20family%20members%20made%20me%20feel%20a%20range%20of%20emotions.%20I%20vividly%20remember%20asking%20my%20father%20about%20the%20December%201992%20incident%20and%20what%20he%20felt%20when%20the%20mob%20demolished%20the%20mosque.%20My%20childhood%20self%20was%20petrified%20and%20frustrated%20with%20the%20imagination%20of%20a%20group%20of%20Hindutva%20leaders%20leading%20a%20mob%20in%20broad%20daylight%20to%20demolishing%20the%20disputed%20structure%2C%20signifying%20a%20vulgar%20display%20of%20majoritarianism.%20In%20hindsight%2C%20I%20would%20read%20my%20question%20as%20an%20inquiry%20about%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20ideals%20on%20which%20this%20state%20was%20built%20by%20its%20makers%20%E2%80%93%20democracy%2C%20secularism%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20father%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20my%20questions%20was%20based%20on%20developments%20at%20the%20time.%20He%20told%20me%20that%20in%201992%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-led%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government%20had%20submitted%20an%20affidavit%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20pledging%20to%20safeguard%20the%20disputed%20structure%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Babri%20mosque.%20Like%20many%20ordinary%20Indians%2C%20he%20believed%20that%20the%20government%20would%20honour%20its%20commitment%20made%20before%20the%20highest%20court%20in%20the%20country.%20As%20a%20child%2C%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20response%20satisfied%20my%20curiosity%20and%20generated%20an%20impression%20that%20a%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98impartial%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98apolitical%E2%80%99%20judiciary%20was%20tricked%20by%20a%20cunning%20and%20majoritarian%20government.%20Muslims%2C%20like%20my%20father%2C%20had%20no%20complaints%20with%20the%20judicial%20process%20but%20with%20how%20the%20promises%20made%20before%20the%20judiciary%20were%20broken%20by%20a%20%E2%80%98rogue%E2%80%99%20government.%20If%20the%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%20judiciary%20had%20its%20day%2C%20it%20would%20have%20checked%20the%20Hindutva%20forces%20from%20creating%20mayhem.%20I%20grew%20up%20internalising%20this%20narrative%20of%20the%20judiciary%20as%20a%20saviour%20in%20the%20face%20of%20majoritarianism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20late%2C%20I%20have%20been%20thinking%20about%20the%20conversations%20I%20had%20with%20my%20father%20back%20then.%20I%20often%20wonder%20how%20I%20would%20respond%20if%20future%20generations%20posed%20a%20similar%20question%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20developments%20of%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20I%20have%20probably%20come%20to%20the%20realisation%20that%20when%20the%20conversation%20with%20the%20past%20fails%20to%20satisfy%20us%2C%20perhaps%20it%E2%80%99s%20best%20for%20our%20sanity%20to%20have%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20future.%20That%20is%20where%20the%20revolutionary%20potential%20lies%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20the%20hope%20for%20it.%20The%20developments%20over%20the%20last%2010%20years%20have%20reshaped%20my%20imagination%20in%20the%20light%20of%20the%20rise%20of%20aggressive%20Hindutva%20politics%20during%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20rule%20in%20India%20since%202014%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20in%20November%202019%20granting%20the%20land%20on%20which%20Babri%20mosque%20stood%20before%20December%201992%20to%20the%20Hindu%20claimants%2C%20and%20more%20recently%2C%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20Rama%20temple%20on%20that%20land%20and%20the%20vulgar%20display%20of%20religious%20supremacy%20surrounding%20the%20%3Cem%3EPran%20Pratishtha%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20present-day%20India%2C%20as%20I%20reflect%20on%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20answers%2C%20the%20vision%20of%20the%20judiciary%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98saviour%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20check%20to%20majoritarian%20oppression%20no%20longer%20holds%20merit.%20It%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20unanimous%20judgment%20allocating%20the%20land%20to%20those%20who%20had%20demolished%20the%20Babri%20Mosque%20ended%20up%20legitimising%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20mosque.%20This%20judgment%20has%20emboldened%20Hindutva%20supremacist%20groups%2C%20fostering%20demands%20for%20the%20conversion%20of%20other%20mosques%20in%20India%20into%20temples%2C%20thereby%20leading%20to%20incidents%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20Babri%20demolition.%20The%20Babri%20judgement%20serves%20as%20a%20microcosm%20of%20institutional%20neglect%20of%20Muslims%2C%20including%20by%20the%20judiciary%20which%20has%20created%20the%20grounds%20for%20the%20continuous%20reproduction%20and%20strengthening%20of%20majoritarian%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%2C%20we%20now%20will%20have%20a%20different%20answer%20to%20offer%20to%20our%20future%20generation.%20This%20articulation%20will%20differ%20from%20facile%20explanations%20of%20the%20current%20situation%20which%20look%20at%20the%20present%20times%20as%20an%20aberration%20to%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20democratic%20history.%20Rather%2C%20we%20will%20perhaps%20better%20understand%20the%20postcolonial%20Indian%20state%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98majoritarian%E2%80%99%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EMinorities%20and%20the%20Making%20of%20Postcolonial%20States%20in%20International%20Law%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EMohammad%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EShahabuddin%20has%20argued%20that%20the%20foundation%20of%20post-colonial%20nation%20states%20rests%20on%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20uniform%20national%20identity%20that%20assimilates%20all%20ethno-cultural%20distinctions.%20Despite%20the%20envisioned%20outcome%20of%20assimilation%20and%20homogenisation%20eradicating%20minority%20issues%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%20the%20actual%20process%20tends%20to%20diminish%20meaningful%20ethno-cultural%20diversity.%20Instead%2C%20it%20reduces%20this%20diversity%20to%20a%20mere%20token%20representation%2C%20imposing%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20majority%20on%20the%20entire%20nation.%20In%20the%20name%20of%20nation-building%20and%20homogenization%2C%20the%20culture%2C%20belief%20system%20and%20cultural%20codes%20of%20the%20majority%20become%20synonymous%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98national%E2%80%99%20identity.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20belief%20that%20the%20minority%20problem%20gets%20resolved%20in%20a%20liberal%20and%20developmental%20state%2C%20the%20postcolonial%20national%20state%20has%20effectively%20served%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20perpetuate%20the%20dominance%20of%20the%20majority%20group%20over%20the%20minority%20across%20political%20and%20cultural%20spheres%2C%20leaving%20the%20minority%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20majority%E2%80%99s%20influence%20on%20crucial%20political%2C%20social%20and%20economic%20matters.%20This%20phenomenon%20is%20not%20exclusive%20to%20India%3B%20similar%20patterns%20can%20be%20observed%20in%20other%20post-colonial%20states%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20deliberations%20within%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20clearly%20demonstrate%20the%20%E2%80%98majoritarian%E2%80%99%20nation%20making%20at%20play%20while%20addressing%20the%20concerns%20associated%20with%20minority%20communities.%20Dr.%20BR%20Ambedkar%2C%20chairperson%20of%20the%20drafting%20committee%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20advocated%20reservations%20to%20minorities%2C%20specifically%20in%20the%20cabinet%20in%20proportion%20to%20their%20population.%20This%20proposal%20was%20presented%20by%20Ambedkar%20in%20his%20memorandum%20titled%20%E2%80%98States%20and%20Minorities%E2%80%99%20and%20submitted%20it%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20in%201946.%20However%2C%20the%20assembly%20rejected%20this%20suggestion%20in%20the%20name%20of%20national%20unity.%20In%20post-partition%20India%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20minority%20representation%20was%20considered%20counterproductive%2C%20linked%20to%20the%20division%20of%20the%20country.%20Despite%20demands%20for%20robust%20and%20meaningful%20safeguards%20for%20minorities%2C%20nationalist%20elites%20rejected%20them%2C%20emphasizing%20the%20goal%20of%20building%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%E2%80%99.%20Thus%2C%20the%20Advisory%20Committee%20abandoned%20reservations%20for%20religious%20minorities%2C%20leaving%20their%20protection%20to%20the%20majority%E2%80%99s%20goodwill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Hindu%20nationalists%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20sought%20a%20constitutional%20ban%20on%20cow%20slaughter%2C%20linking%20it%20to%20Hindu%20religious%20sentiments%2C%20Muslim%20members%20highlighted%20the%20inconsistency%20within%20the%20prevailing%20liberal%20secular%20rhetoric%20in%20the%20assembly%2C%20which%20was%20unwilling%20to%20accommodate%20the%20concerns%20of%20religious%20minorities.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20the%20assembly%20included%20a%20directive%20principle%20prohibiting%20cow%20slaughter%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20blending%20religious%20sentiments%20with%20cultural%20and%20economic%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prevalence%20of%20majoritarian%20views%20in%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20minority%20rights%20tells%20us%20that%20post-colonial%20India%20was%20%E2%80%98conceived%E2%80%99%20as%20a%20majoritarian%20state.%20It%20should%20not%20surprise%20us%20that%20the%20judiciary%20too%20became%20an%20arena%20where%20these%20pro-majoritarian%20values%20got%20reinforced.%20In%20fact%2C%20judicial%20pronouncements%20signal%20an%20end%20to%20political%20discourse%20because%20the%20judiciary%20has%20the%20ability%20to%20speak%20the%20final%20word.%20By%20taking%20matters%20to%20the%20judiciary%2C%20we%20limit%20the%20scope%20and%20chances%20of%20political%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20India%20is%20witnessing%20brute%20Hindutva%20majoritarianism%2C%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98neutrality%E2%80%99%20of%20institutions%20stands%20exposed.%20It%20is%20for%20everyone%20to%20see%20how%20putative%20%E2%80%98democratic%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%20institutions%20have%20given%20way%20to%20power.%20The%20fact%20is%20that%20the%20terms%20of%20%E2%80%98neutrality%E2%80%99%20were%20fixed%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20making%20of%20the%20constitution.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20our%20institutions%20are%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20what%20constitutes%20%E2%80%98neutrality%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98fairness%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98non-arbitrariness%E2%80%99%20was%20circumscribed%20by%20majoritarianism.%20The%20present%20times%20are%20no%20aberration.%20The%20exclusion%20of%20minorities%20was%20well-entrenched%20in%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20author%20is%20Assistant%20Professor%2C%20Dr.%20Ram%20Manohar%20Lohiya%20National%20Law%20University%2C%20Lucknow.%C2%A0%20He%20thanks%20Haris%20Jamil%20and%20Priya%20Anuragini%20for%20their%20comments.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707745233000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F27153406%2Fbabri_masjid-11302_2486082a-e1563521469520.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmosque-temple-and-the-neutrality-of-indian-institutions-reflections-of-an-ordinary-muslim%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20a%20time%20when%20India%20is%20witnessing%20brute%20Hindutva%20majoritarianism%2C%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98neutrality%E2%80%99%20of%20institutions%20stands%20exposed.%20It%20is%20for%20everyone%20to%20see%20how%20putative%20%E2%80%98democratic%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%20institutions%20have%20given%20way%20to%20power.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmosque-temple-and-the-neutrality-of-indian-institutions-reflections-of-an-ordinary-muslim%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Roc%C3%ADo%20San