to%20Qatar%20on%20February%2014%2C%20after%20his%20visit%20to%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20Foreign%20Secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra%20announced%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20announcement%20comes%20within%20a%20day%20of%20news%20breaking%20that%20after%2018%20months%20of%20detention%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fqatar-emir-pardons-navy-indians-released%5C%22%3EQatar%20had%20released%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20eight%20former%20Indian%20naval%20veterans%20who%20had%20been%20convicted%20to%20death%20and%20later%20imprisoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20the%20UAE%20was%20anticipated%2C%20his%20unexpected%20stop%20in%20Qatar%20comes%20as%20a%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20UAE%2C%20he%20will%20be%20inaugurating%20a%20Hindu%20temple%2C%20give%20a%20speech%20at%20the%20World%20Governance%20Summit%20and%20attend%20an%20Indian%20community%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20completing%20his%20UAE%20visit%2C%20on%20February%2014%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20will%20travel%20to%20Doha%2C%20Qatar%20on%20February%2014%20afternoon.%20During%20the%20visit%20the%20prime%20minister%20will%20hold%20bilateral%20talks%20with%20Sheikh%20Tamim%20Bin%20Hamad%2C%20the%20Amir%20of%20Qatar%20and%20other%20high%20dignitaries%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kwatra%20said%20at%20a%20special%20media%20briefing%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20being%20asked%20by%20reporters%20as%20to%20whether%20Modi%20is%20visiting%20Qatar%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20release%20of%20the%20veterans%2C%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra%20said%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20visits%20are%20scheduled%20for%20months%20in%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20gratified%20on%20their%20return.%20We%20deeply%20appreciate%20the%20decision%20of%20Qatar%E2%80%99s%20government%20and%20the%20Amir%20to%20release%20them.%20We%20are%20happy%20to%20have%20seven%20of%20those%20Indian%20nationals%20back.%20The%20eighth%20Indian%20national%20has%20also%20been%20released%20and%20we%20continue%20to%20work%20with%20the%20Qatar%20government%20to%20see%20how%20quickly%20his%20return%20to%20India%20would%20be%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeven%20of%20them%20arrived%20in%20the%20early%20hours%20of%20Monday%2C%20while%20the%20eighth%20former%20naval%20officer%2C%20Commodore%20Purnendu%20Tiwari%2C%20opted%20to%20stay%20behind%20temporarily%20to%20finalize%20the%20necessary%20formalities%20for%20his%20return%2C%20given%20that%20his%20family%20had%20been%20settled%20in%20Qatar%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20seven%20veterans%20who%20are%20now%20back%20in%20India%20are%20Captain%20Navtej%20Singh%20Gill%2C%20Captain%20Birendra%20Kumar%20Verma%2C%20Captain%20Saurabh%20Vasisht%2C%20Commodore%20Amit%20Nagpal%2C%20Commodore%20Sugunakar%20Pakala%2C%20Commodore%20Sanjeev%20Gupta%20and%20Sailor%20Ragesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20as%20to%20whether%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20had%20been%20key%20in%20the%20men%20securing%20a%20pardon%20from%20the%20Qatar%20Emir%2C%20Kwatra%20said%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20had%20been%20monitoring%20the%20situation%20constantly%20and%20did%20not%20shy%20away%20from%20taking%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20prime%20minister%20has%20himself%20personally%20constantly%20supervised%20all%20the%20developments%20in%20this%20case%20and%20has%20never%20shied%20away%20from%20any%20initiatives%20that%20would%20ensure%20the%20return%20of%20the%20Indian%20nationals%20back%20to%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eight%20naval%20veterans%2C%20who%20had%20been%20detained%20since%20August%202022%2C%20were%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fqatar-eight-former-indian-navy-officers-handed-death-penalty%5C%22%3Esentenced%20to%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20Qatar%E2%80%99s%20Court%20of%20First%20Instance%20on%20October%2026%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20had%20a%20small%20chat%20the%20Emir%20of%20Qatar%2C%20Tamim%20ibn%20Hamad%20Al%20Thani%2C%20at%20the%20COP%20summit%20in%20Dubai%20in%20December%2C%20but%20no%20details%20publicly%20released%20about%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20conversation%20beyond%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1730879676875481375%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Etweet%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20freed%20men%20%E2%80%93%20seven%20of%20whom%20returned%20today%20and%20who%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faninews.in%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Fwouldnt-have-been-possible-freed-navy-vets-chant-bharat-mata-ki-jai-praise-pm-modi-on-return-from-qatar20240212064803%2F%5C%22%3Espoke%20to%20the%20news%20agency%20ANI%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20said%20that%20it%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20were%20it%20not%20for%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20another%20question%20on%20whether%20the%20Qatari%20Emir%20had%20released%20the%20Indian%20nationals%20with%20a%20pardon%2C%20the%20foreign%20secretary%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20can%20talk%20about%20different%20terminology%20etc..%20whether%20it%20is%20a%20release%20or%20pardon..but%20I%20think%20we%20should%20see%20the%20facts%20for%20what%20they%20are.%20Seven%20of%20the%20eight%20Indian%20nationals%20in%20the%20Al%20Dahra%20case%20are%20back%20in%20India%2C%20back%20to%20their%20homes%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kwatra%20replied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MEA%20press%20release%20had%20also%20shied%20away%20from%20using%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98pardon%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20would%20mean%20that%20the%20veterans%20were%20guilty%20of%20the%20charges%2C%20which%20have%20yet%20not%20been%20made%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707734313000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02122720%2Fthani-modi.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnavy-veterans-release-narendra-modi-qatar%2