cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fjokowi-effect-how-indonesias-outgoing-leader-shaped-election-to-succeed-him%2Famp_articleshow%2F107625069.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fjokowi-effect-how-indonesias-outgoing-leader-shaped-election-to-succeed-him%2Famp_articleshow%2F107625069.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Fashionable%20to%20Demolish%20Houses%20Without%20Due%20Procedure%2C%20Should%20Be%20Last%20Recourse%E2%80%99%3A%20MP%20High%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F16172609%2FUntitled-design-2021-07-16T172559.085.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20a%20case%20regarding%20illegal%20demolition%20of%20houses%2C%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20high%20court%20has%20directed%20%E2%80%9Cdisciplinary%20action%E2%80%9D%20against%20the%20concerned%20municipal%20authorities%20and%20awarded%20Rs%201%20lakh%20in%20compensation%20to%20the%20petitioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%2C%20Radha%20Langri%2C%20had%20approached%20the%20court%20seeking%20compensation%20for%20the%20demolition%20of%20her%20houses%20carried%20out%20without%20following%20due%20procedure%20by%20the%20Ujjain%20Municipal%20Corporation%20(UMC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Vivek%20Rusia%2C%20while%20delivering%20the%20ruling%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20observed%20repeatedly%20by%20this%20court%2C%20it%20has%20become%20fashionable%20now%20for%20local%20administration%20and%20local%20bodies%20to%20demolish%20any%20house%20by%20drawing%20up%20proceedings%20without%20complying%20with%20the%20Principal%20of%20Natural%20Justice%20and%20publish%20it%20in%20the%20newspaper.%20It%20appears%20that%20in%20this%20case%20also%20the%20criminal%20case%20was%20registered%20against%20one%20of%20the%20family%20members%20of%20the%20petitioners%20and%20demolition%20activities%20were%20carried%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUMC%20argued%20that%20the%20demolitions%20were%20justified%20as%20the%20houses%20(house%20no.%20466%20and%20467)%20had%20been%20constructed%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20Municipal%20Corporation%20Act%20since%20the%20petitioners%20had%20not%20obtained%20building%20permission%20beforehand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20while%20no%20one%20has%20the%20right%20to%20construct%20a%20house%20without%20proper%20permission%2C%20demolition%20should%20be%20considered%20as%20a%20last%20resort.%20Moreover%2C%20it%20should%20only%20be%20carried%20out%20after%20providing%20the%20house%20owner%20with%20a%20fair%20chance%20to%20rectify%20the%20situation%20by%20obtaining%20regularisation%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fhigh-court%2Fmadhya-pradesh-high-court%2Ffashionable-now-to-demolish-houses-without-complying-with-principles-of-natural-justice-demolition-should-be-the-last-recourse-mp-high-court-249130%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmuslims-targeted-in-128-demolitions-617-people-affected-amnesty-reports-on-bulldozer-action%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Muslims%20Targeted%20in%20128%20Demolitions%2C%20617%20People%20Affected%E2%80%99%3A%20Amnesty%20Reports%20on%20Bulldozer%20Action%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20pointed%20out%20discrepancies%20in%20the%20ownership%20details%20of%20the%20houses%20and%20noted%20that%20a%20fabricated%20%3Cem%3Epanchnama%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20been%20prepared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UMC%20alleged%20that%20house%20no.%20466%20was%20owned%20by%20one%20Parvez%20Khan%2C%20not%20Langri%2C%20and%20the%20other%20was%20registered%20under%20one%20Uma.%20However%2C%20the%20court%20found%20that%20no%20one%20by%20the%20name%20of%20Parvez%20Khan%20exists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fhigh-court%2Fmadhya-pradesh-high-court%2Ffashionable-now-to-demolish-houses-without-complying-with-principles-of-natural-justice-demolition-should-be-the-last-recourse-mp-high-court-249130%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CHad%20the%20building%20officer%20gone%20to%20the%20spot%20he%20would%20have%20been%20informed%20about%20the%20name%20of%20the%20petitioner%20about%20the%20ownership.%20There%20is%20no%20such%20person%20in%20the%20name%20of%20Parvez%20Khan%2C%20there%20is%20no%20such%20document%20to%20show%20that%20he%20purchased%20the%20property%20only%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20this%20so%20called%20oral%20information%20the%20panchnama%20was%20drawn%20and%20drastic%20action%20for%20demolition%20has%20been%20taken.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20demolition%20of%20house%20no.%20466%20by%20serving%20a%20notice%20to%20a%20fictitious%20person%20Parvez%20Khan%20is%20a%20highly%20illegal%20and%20arbitrary%20action%20for%20which%20disciplinary%20action%20is%20liable%20to%20be%20taken%20against%20the%20concerned%20officers%20and%20employee%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20remarked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20house%20no.%20467%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20demolition%20notice%20was%20issued%20to%20Uma%20in%20a%20careless%20manner%20and%20without%20any%20acknowledgment.%20The%20bench%20pulled%20up%20the%20corporation%20authorities%20over%20the%20lack%20of%20proper%20procedure%20and%20arbitrary%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%20were%20also%20given%20the%20option%20to%20seek%20further%20compensation%20for%20their%20losses%20through%20a%20civil%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBulldozer%20action%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternational%20human%20rights%20organisation%20Amnesty%20International%2C%20last%20week%2C%20released%20two%20reports%20titled%20%E2%80%98If%20you%20speak%20up%2C%20your%20house%20will%20be%20demolished%E2%80%99%3A%20Bulldozer%20Injustice%20in%20India%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Unearthing%20Accountability%3A%20JCB%E2%80%99s%20Role%20and%20Responsibility%20in%20Bulldozer%20Injustice%20in%20India%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reports%20document%20the%20punitive%20demolition%20of%20Muslim%20properties%20in%20at%20least%20five%20states%20using%20JCB-branded%20bulldozers%20calling%20it%20%E2%80%9Ca%20hate%20campaign%20against%20the%20minority%20community%E2%80%9D.%20According%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20demolitions%2C%20often%20enacted%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20removing%20illegal%20construction%2C%20violated%20due%20process%20outlined%20in%20domestic%20and%20international%20human%20rights%20law.%20They%20also%20highlighted%20that%20Muslim-concentrated%20localities%20were%20targeted%2C%20while%20Muslim-owned%20properties%20were%20selectively%20demolished%2C%20leaving%20nearby%20Hindu-owned%20properties%20untouched.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707727824000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F16172609%2FUntitled-design-2021-07-16T172559.085.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffashionable-to-demolish-houses-without-due-procedure-should-be-last-recourse-mp-high-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3B%5BDemolition%5D%20should%20only%20be%20carried%20out%20after%20providing%20the%20house%20owner%20with%20a%20fair%20chance%20to%20rectify%20the%20situation%20by%20obtaining%20regularisation%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20remarked.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffashionable-to-demolish-houses-without-due-procedure-should-be-last-recourse-mp-high-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Do%20Trinamool%20Congress's%20Rajya%20Sabha%20Nominations%20Say%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F12124835%2FUntitled-design-9-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWest%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20party%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%2C%20on%20Sunday%2C%20named%20four%20Rajya%20Sabha%20nominees%20of%20the%20party%20for%20the%20coming%20February%2027%20election%2C%20a%20list%20that%20reflected%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20national%2C%20regional%20and%20local%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFive%20Rajya%20Sabha%20seats%20from%20West%20Bengal%20are%20falling%20vacant%20and%20the%20victory%20of%20the%20TMC%20is%20certain%20in%20four%20while%20the%20other%20is%20set%20to%20go%20to%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20BJP%20on%20the%20same%20day%20named%20state%20unit%20veteran%20Samik%20Bhattacharya%2C%20a%20former%20MLA%20and%20the%20state%20unit%E2%80%99s%20chief%20spokesperson%2C%20as%20its%20nominee.%20This%20is%20being%20seen%20as%20a%20gesture%20to%20BJP%20%E2%80%98old-timers%E2%80%99%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20have%20recently%20been%20offended%20or%20upset%20by%20the%20growing%20influence%20of%20%E2%80%98newcomers%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20state%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20surprise%20inclusion%20in%20the%20TMC%20list%20was%20senior%20Delhi-based%20journalist%20Sagarika%20Ghose%2C%20while%20senior%20Assam%20leader%20Sushmita%20Dev%20is%20being%20sent%20to%20the%20Upper%20House%20again%2C%20after%20a%20brief%20break%20of%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20two%20other%20TMC%20nominees%20are%20Mamata%20Thakur%2C%20a%20former%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20and%20prominent%20leader%20of%20the%20refugee%20Matua%20community%2C%20and%20Mohammed%20Nadimul%20Haque%2C%20the%20owner%20and%20editor%20of%20Akhbar-e-Mashriq%2C%20one%20of%20West%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20most%20influential%20Urdu%20dailies.%20Haque%2C%20who%20was%20first%20sent%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20in%202012%2C%20got%20a%20straight%20third%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CToday%E2%80%99s%20list%20of%20candidates%20has%20two%20very%20important%20messages.%20Three%20out%20of%20the%20four%20are%20women.%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20is%20sending%20more%20women%20to%20the%20parliament.%20We%20do%20not%20know%20when%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20law%20passed%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20will%20be%20implemented%20but%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20is%20walking%20the%20talk%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dev%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20after%20the%20announcement%20a%20day%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20TMC%20currently%20has%20Dola%20Sen%20and%20Mausam%20Noor%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20the%20inclusion%20of%20three%20more%20would%20mean%20five%20out%20of%2013%20TMC%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MPs%20are%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20other%20message%20was%2C%20Dev%20said%20regarding%20her%20nomination%2C%20that%20this%20was%20the%20first%20time%20that%20a%20politician%20from%20the%20northeast%20has%20been%20twice%20sent%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20from%20outside%20the%20northeast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESagarika%20Ghose%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20TMC%20veterans%2C%20the%20nomination%20of%20Ghose%20reflects%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20ambition%20to%20have%20prominent%20%E2%80%98liberal%20faces%E2%80%99%20addressing%20the%20national%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Rajya%20Sabha%20team%20already%20includes%20Jawhar%20Sircar%2C%20former%20Prasar%20Bharati%20CEO%20and%20India%20culture%20secretary%2C%20and%20Delhi-based%20journalist-turned-Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20activist%20Saket%20Gokhale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGhose%2C%20who%20has%20played%20leading%20roles%20both%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20print%20and%20broadcast%20media%2C%20has%20authored%2C%20among%20other%20books%2C%20%3Cem%3E