%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAround%2015%20women%20have%20been%20employed%20to%20upcycle%20discarded%20jeans%20into%20warm%20sleeping%20bags.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20process%20of%20stitching%20a%20sleeping%20bag%2C%20Nirvaan%20says%20one%20sleeping%20bag%20needs%20seven%20old%20jeans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20the%20jeans%20are%20cleaned%20and%20washed.%20Then%2C%20the%20belt%20and%20zip%20portion%20of%20the%20jeans%20are%20cut.%20The%20legs%20are%20cut%20into%20long%20strips%20and%20sewn%20together.%20Then%20a%20cloth%20lining%20is%20added%20inside%20for%20comfort%20along%20with%20a%20foam%20layer%20for%20insulation.%20The%20lining%20is%20filled%20using%20fabric%20scraps%20from%20Shivani%E2%80%99s%20boutique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Project%20Jeans%20employs%2015%20local%20women%2C%20including%20wives%20of%20tailors%20from%20Shivani%E2%80%99s%20unit%20and%20others%20from%20Rajokri%20village%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Each%20bag%20costs%20Rs%20800%20to%20make%2C%20which%20includes%20Rs%20500%20labour%20cost%2C%20Rs%20250%20for%20the%20foam%2C%20Rs%2025%20for%20the%20zip%20and%20Rs%2025%20for%20other%20overheads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENirvaan%20says%20that%20they%20have%20distributed%202%2C000%20bags%20so%20far.%20They%20also%20sent%20200%20sleeping%20bags%20to%20Turkey%20and%20Syria%20in%202023%20for%20those%20impacted%20by%20the%20earthquake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20repurposed%20over%20120%20million%20litres%20of%20water%2C%20which%20would%20have%20been%20required%20to%20make%20these%20bags%20otherwise.%20We%20are%20saving%2070%2C000%20litres%20of%20water%20per%20bag%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiscussing%20the%20carbon%20emissions%20in%20the%20life%20cycle%20of%20jeans%2C%20he%20mentions%20that%20it%20takes%2033.4%20kg%20to%20produce%20one%20pair.%20He%20proudly%20states%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20repurposed%20over%204%20lakh